results.notes: The canonical definition perfectly matches the UBX-INF-WARNING message as described in the provided u-blox 8/u-blox M8 Receiver description - Manual (UBX-13003221-R28). The variable-length payload of ASCII characters is correctly represented using a repeated group with 'fill_remaining' repetition type. Supported protocol versions also align, with the canonical's minimum protocol version (1800) being well within the range specified in the manual.

discrepancies.issue: Canonical's minimum supported protocol version is higher than specified in the PDF.
